Executive Profile
Leroy C. Richie  Of Counsel, Lewis & Munday PCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 74 Board Members in 74 different organizations across 100 different industries.See Board Relationships76--
Background

		Mr. Leroy C. Richie, also known as Roy, has been the Of Counsel at Lewis & Munday PC since 1987 and its Counsel since 2004. Mr. Richie has over twenty years of legal experience. He served as a Vice President and General Counsel of Automotive Legal Affairs of Chrysler Corporation from 1990 to 1997, where he directed all legal affairs for that its automotive operations. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Q Standards Worldwide, Inc., and Capital Coating ... Technologies, Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Highland Park Michigan Economic Development Corp. He served as a Vice Chairman of Detroit Medical Center and the Detroit Economic Growth Corp. He has been an Independent Director of Columbia Seligman Communications and Information Fund, Inc since November 2008. He has been a Trustee of Columbia Seligman Premium Technology Growth Fund, Inc. since October 2009 and Columbia Funds Series Trust II - Columbia Seligman Communications and Information Fund since June 2011. He serves as Independent Trustee of Columbia Funds Trust III - Columbia Mid Cap Value Fund. He has been Director and Lead Outside Director of Digital Ally Inc. since September 1, 2005. He has been an Independent Director of Tri-Continental Corporation since 2000. He serves as a member of the board of directors of the mutual fund family managed by Ameriprise Financial, Inc., Vibration Control Technologies, LLC, Great Lakes Assemblies, LLC and Gulf Shore Assemblies, LLC. He serves as an Independent Trustee/Director of various funds in combined fund complex of RiverSource Funds, Columbia Funds, Nations Funds and Threadneedle Funds. He has been an Independent Director at Infinity Energy Resources Inc. since June 1, 1999 and served as its Lead Outside Director. Mr. Richie served as a Director of Oklahoma Gas and Electric Company and Infinity, Inc. He served as an Independent Director of Columbia Frontier Fund Inc., since November 2008. Mr. Richie served as an Independent Director of OGE Energy Corp. since November 2007 until May 15, 2014. He served as a Director of Kerr-McGee Corporation since 1998. He served as a Director/ Trustee of various funds in the fund complex of Seligman funds. He was a Trustee of New York University Law Center Foundation. Mr. Richie holds a BA degree from City College of New York and a JD from the New York University School of Law, where he was awarded an Arthur Garfield Hays Civil Liberties Fellowship.Read Full Background




